article.headline: St. Francis, NY 65, Wagner 62
article.story: NEW YORK -- Jamaal Womack score 17 points and St. Francis, N.Y., snapped a three-game losing streak with a 65-62 win over Wagner on Thursday night. Stefan Perunicic added 12 points, all on 3-pointers, for the Terriers (5-13, 3-5 Northeast) and John Gooden scored 11. Jamal Smith led the visiting Seahawks (10-8, 3-5) with 21 points and Joey Mundweiler scored 15. Mundweiler's 3-pointer gave Wagner a 60-58 lead with 3:56 to play, but St. Francis outscored the Seahawks 7-2 the rest of the way. Justin Newton made two free throws with 1:51 to put the Terriers ahead for good, 61-60.
